## Section I: PREAMBLE

This OpenRAIL-S License is generally applicable to the **judge-gym** Source Code. The “Open” nomenclature indicates that the Source Code is freely accessible. The “RAIL” nomenclature indicates that there are use-based restrictions intended to prevent the misuse of generative epistemics for automated political enforcement or the hallucination of consensus in contested domains.

NOW THEREFORE, You and Licensor agree as follows:

### 1. Definitions

(a) **"Contribution"** means any software code or modifications submitted to Licensor.
(b) **"Contributor"** means Licensor and any entity that has contributed to the Source Code.
(c) **“Data”** means information extracted from datasets used with a Model.
(d) **“Derivatives”** means all works containing additions or modifications to the Source Code.
(e) **“Harm”** includes physical, mental, psychological, financial, and reputational damage.
(f) **"License"** means the terms and conditions defined in this document.
(g) **“Licensor”** means the rights owner granting the License.
(h) **“Model”** means any machine-learning based assemblies used with the Source Code.
(i) **“Source Code”** means the judge-gym collection of text, scripts, and engine components.
(j) **“Third Parties”** means individuals or entities not under common control with Licensor.
(k) **"You"** means an individual or entity exercising permissions granted by this License.

